AQZ.AX.summary: Alliance Aviation Services Limited provides aviation services to tourism, resources, mining, education, government, corporate, and sporting sectors in Australia and internationally. The company also offers specialized aviation services, including aircraft wet leasing, airport management, aircraft trading, parts sales, engine leasing, and engineering to other airlines and clients. As of June 30, 2020, it operated a fleet of 24 Fokker F100 and 13 Fokker 70LR jet aircraft; and 5 Fokker 50 turboprops. The company was founded in 2002 and is based in Brisbane, Australia.

QABSY.summary: Qantas Airways Limited provides passenger and freight air transportation services in Australia and internationally. The company also offers air cargo and express freight services; and customer loyalty programs. As of June 30, 2020, it operated a fleet of 314 aircraft under the Qantas and Jetstar brands. The company was founded in 1920 and is headquartered in Mascot, Australia.

R4L.F.summary: Regional Express Holdings Limited engages in the air transportation of passengers and freight. The company operates through Regular Public Transport and Charter segments. It provides aeromedical transport services; fly in/fly out charter services; airfreight charter services; and corporate jet charter services. The company also offers training programs to students and other airlines; and airline cadet pilot training for global carriers. As of September 30, 2020, it operated a fleet of 60 Saab 340 aircraft on approximately 1,500 weekly flights to 59 destinations throughout all states in Australia. The company was formerly known as Australiawide Airlines Limited and changed its name to Regional Express Holdings Limited in 2005. Regional Express Holdings Limited was founded in 1953 and is based in Mascot, Australia.
